# Container Management API Testing
# Use this file to test all API endpoints

### 1. Get all ports
GET http://localhost:5000/api/ports

### 2. Get all statuses
GET http://localhost:5000/api/statuses

### 3. Create test containers for Manila Port
POST http://localhost:5000/api/containers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "statusId": 1,
  "type": "20ft Standard",
  "containerDesc": "Standard shipping container for general cargo",
  "currentPortId": 1
}

### 4. Create another container
POST http://localhost:5000/api/containers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "statusId": 2,
  "type": "40ft High Cube",
  "containerDesc": "High cube container for oversized cargo",
  "currentPortId": 1
}

### 5. Create third container
POST http://localhost:5000/api/containers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "statusId": 1,
  "type": "20ft Refrigerated",
  "containerDesc": "Refrigerated container for perishable goods",
  "currentPortId": 1
}

### 6. Get containers for Manila Port (should show 3 containers)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/containers/port/1

### 7. Get Manila Port yards
GET http://localhost:5000/api/yards/port/1

### 8. Get blocks for Manila Yard 1
GET http://localhost:5000/api/blocks/yard/1

### 9. Get bays for Block 1
GET http://localhost:5000/api/bays/block/1

### 10. Get rows for Bay A
GET http://localhost:5000/api/rows/bay/1

### 11. Get slots for Row 1
GET http://localhost:5000/api/slots/row/1

### 12. Move container CON-1 to Block 1, Bay A, Row 1, Tier 1
PUT http://localhost:5000/api/containers/1/location
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "yardId": 1,
  "blockId": 1,
  "bayId": 1,
  "rowId": 1,
  "tier": 1
}

### 13. Move container CON-2 to Block 1, Bay A, Row 1, Tier 2 (should work - FILO)
PUT http://localhost:5000/api/containers/2/location
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "yardId": 1,
  "blockId": 1,
  "bayId": 1,
  "rowId": 1,
  "tier": 2
}

### 14. Try to move CON-3 to Tier 4 (should fail - FILO violation)
PUT http://localhost:5000/api/containers/3/location
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "yardId": 1,
  "blockId": 1,
  "bayId": 1,
  "rowId": 1,
  "tier": 4
}

### 15. Move CON-3 to Tier 3 (should work)
PUT http://localhost:5000/api/containers/3/location
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "yardId": 1,
  "blockId": 1,
  "bayId": 1,
  "rowId": 1,
  "tier": 3
}

### 16. Search for container by number
GET http://localhost:5000/api/containers/search/CON-1

### 17. Get container location hierarchy
GET http://localhost:5000/api/containers/1/location-hierarchy

### 18. Get all containers again (should show updated locations)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/containers/port/1